{
  "text": "Operative repair has been largely replaced by image-guided occlusion for iatrogenic femoral PSAs. [CITATION_1] Spontaneous femoral PSAs are extremely rare, and only a few cases have been described in medical literature. We report a large spontaneous PSA of the distal part of a superficial femoral artery (SFA) which was successfully treated with covered stents.",
  "citation_candidates": [
